Methodology
83 elderly patients (age ≥60 years) with depression were evaluated on GDS-30, BDI, GAD-7 and PHQ-15.
Results
60 subjects (72.28%) had GAD-7 score of ≥10, which is indicative of significant anxiety. On PHQ-15, 98.8% of patients had moderate to severe somatization. There was no correlation between severity of depressive symptoms (as assessed by GDS-30 and BDI) with anxiety and depressive symptoms except for significant correlation between BDI total score and GAD-7 total score (Pearson correlation coefficient-0.319;p = 0.003).Factor analysis of GDS-30 yielded a five factor solution and when the items of other 3 scales were added, the number of factors/symptoms clusters increased to 7.
