Results
41 patients (20 in the escitalopram group and 21 in the sertraline group) completed the trial. In the escitalopram group 15 (70%) patients and in the sertraline group 16 (76.19%) patients showed more than 34% decrease in mean YBOCS score at the end of the trial (P=0.531). The two groups revealed significant decrease in YBOCS scores without significant difference (P=0.861) at week 12. No serious adverse effects were reported.
