Results
Correlations between impulsive behavior and psychosocial variables were examined. A significant association between level of impulsive behavior and severity of psychopathological symptoms was observed (P=0.0001). Young age (P=0.001), male patients (P=0.0001) and those with history of childhood sexual or physical abuse (P=0.0001), were more impulsive. Linear regression (step wise) analysis model showed that male sex (P=0.001), positive symptoms (P=0.006), and childhood physical abuse (P=0.001) were significant associations.
